33:07.786 --> 33:09.231
I'm not the type who gets stuck.

33:09.421 --> 33:12.459
Anyway... l can arrange for your money.

33:13.058 --> 33:16.267
Very good!

33:17.095 --> 33:18.073
Thank you.

33:20.732 --> 33:21.472
Joseph.

33:22.501 --> 33:24.344
- How much do we have?
- Earlier, there were 200.

33:24.403 --> 33:25.438
- And now..
- I'm talking about cash.

33:25.504 --> 33:28.508
Sir, thank God you've come.

33:28.840 --> 33:30.410
It now feels like
things will get better.

33:30.475 --> 33:31.749
We're scared.

33:31.910 --> 33:34.186
Please tell us what to do.

33:34.880 --> 33:35.790
Sir...

33:58.870 --> 34:02.010
Joseph, make a list of our
staff and their families.

34:02.240 --> 34:04.186
See if we can accommodate
everyone here.

34:04.309 --> 34:05.845
Otherwise,
we'll make other arrangements.

34:07.212 --> 34:08.213
Relax everyone.

34:09.380 --> 34:10.324
Sit.

34:12.050 --> 34:12.994
Relax.

34:16.420 --> 34:17.831
What do you think you're doing?

34:17.889 --> 34:19.869
Why aren't you getting us out of here?

34:20.225 --> 34:22.728
I can't just desert them, can I?

34:23.862 --> 34:25.341
But you can desert us.

34:26.197 --> 34:28.906
Don't you have any
responsibility towards us?

34:29.134 --> 34:30.135
Of course I do.

34:30.469 --> 34:32.210
But these people work for me.

34:33.038 --> 34:34.277
They have the same
expectations from us...

34:34.339 --> 34:36.341
as we did
the Kuwaiti government.

34:41.846 --> 34:43.416
How can anyone run from
their responsibilities...

34:43.481 --> 34:45.154
- these were your words.
- Yes, they were.

34:45.350 --> 34:47.159
But it's easy to make tall claims.

34:47.319 --> 34:48.389
That was my mistake.

34:48.753 --> 34:50.322
But you're making an even bigger one.

34:50.388 --> 34:51.924
And why this sudden
urge to be a Messiah?

34:51.989 --> 34:53.969
I have no interest in being a Messiah.

34:55.827 --> 34:57.101
I too want to get us out of here.

34:57.929 --> 35:00.239
But... once I make
some arrangements for them.

35:17.449 --> 35:19.292
Take care of yourselves.

35:19.584 --> 35:22.224
Soon we'll make some arrangements.

35:22.554 --> 35:23.862
Did you eat?

35:24.823 --> 35:26.131
Did you eat?

35:40.872 --> 35:42.374
Give me some space.

35:42.607 --> 35:44.143
Where do you expect me to sleep?

35:44.442 --> 35:45.614
Strange problem.

35:45.877 --> 35:46.582
Calm down.

35:46.878 --> 35:49.484
Isn't there enough of
a battle for space outside?

35:49.548 --> 35:50.925
Stop being childish.

35:50.982 --> 35:52.393
Come here.
Here.

35:52.517 --> 35:53.427
Come on.

35:54.386 --> 35:57.299
There's space here.

36:54.212 --> 36:55.190
Excuse me.

36:55.914 --> 36:57.689
The toilets have become very dirty.

36:58.250 --> 36:59.627
They're stinking.

37:00.952 --> 37:02.192
You're the <i>boss,</i> aren't you?

37:02.787 --> 37:04.323
That's why I am telling you.

37:04.756 --> 37:06.167
- Do you work here?
- No!

37:06.224 --> 37:08.261
Hey come here.

37:08.994 --> 37:11.406
Let me know when it's clean.

37:11.796 --> 37:13.332
I'm in this room.

37:13.698 --> 37:15.700
Hey, move aside.

37:16.234 --> 37:17.645
I'm not going to be called a refugee
along with these drivers and coolies...

37:17.702 --> 37:19.704
- Sir, any problem?

37:20.338 --> 37:22.215
- Who is he?
- I don't know, sir.

37:22.707 --> 37:24.209
Around 100 more came here last night.

37:24.409 --> 37:25.820
There are many like him.

37:26.011 --> 37:28.457
More than 1000 Indians
are waiting outside.

37:30.148 --> 37:31.024
How did they get here?

37:31.082 --> 37:33.688
Sir, they say they're friends,
relatives, etcetera...

37:33.752 --> 37:35.163
of our employees.

37:35.220 --> 37:36.164
They had nowhere to go.

37:36.254 --> 37:37.665
So they came here...

37:37.722 --> 37:39.360
because they feel
safer when they're together.

37:41.893 --> 37:45.397
Sir... it's hard to arrange
food for 500 people.

37:45.797 --> 37:47.902
What will we do with 1600?

37:49.434 --> 37:51.436
If you want, I can identify
those who work for us...

37:51.669 --> 37:53.478
and ask the rest to leave?

37:55.440 --> 37:56.248
No!

38:09.854 --> 38:11.128
Hello, sir.

38:12.357 --> 38:13.301
This way.

38:18.229 --> 38:19.970
Wasn't Ranjit heading here?

38:20.598 --> 38:22.669
But I heard the situation
is pretty bad in the city center.

38:24.703 --> 38:26.046
- Hello, everyone.
- Hello.

38:26.171 --> 38:27.582
- Hey, Ranjit.
- He's here.

38:27.806 --> 38:28.614
How are you?

38:29.040 --> 38:29.984
Thank you.

38:30.775 --> 38:33.119
Ranjit, you too?
In the day?

38:33.244 --> 38:35.815
Saddam has turned
everything on its head.

38:37.115 --> 38:39.755
Ranjit, when all
this is over tomorrow...

38:39.951 --> 38:43.194
you'll have an exciting
story to tell your grandchildren.

38:43.354 --> 38:46.665
Like "When uncle Saddam
was swirling Kuwait around..."

38:46.891 --> 38:50.304
l was swirling a glass of
scotch in Kurien uncle's supermarket.

38:50.929 --> 38:52.931
- So it'll all be over tomorrow?
- Of course, Ranjit.

38:53.131 --> 38:54.405
You think America will stay quiet?

38:54.766 --> 38:56.109
So what is America waiting for?

38:56.201 --> 38:58.010
For us to finish our scotch.

38:58.203 --> 38:59.614
Calm down, Ranjit.

38:59.804 --> 39:01.283
They'll keep us afraid of
the villain for a couple of days.

39:01.339 --> 39:03.979
Then tell the Arabs,
'look at what happened to Kuwait.'

39:04.242 --> 39:06.244
'Let us in... build a military base.'

39:06.344 --> 39:07.288
'And we'll keep you safe.'

39:07.345 --> 39:09.154
And everything will
be back to business.

39:09.214 --> 39:10.318
It's a question of a few days.

39:11.149 --> 39:13.925
So gentlemen, this is everything.

39:13.985 --> 39:15.726
You guys can take what you want.

39:15.787 --> 39:16.424
Ranjit.

39:16.654 --> 39:18.133
- Ibrahim.
- Yes, sir.

39:18.189 --> 39:21.170
Ranjit sir... l'm sure
you haven't brought a truck.

39:21.226 --> 39:22.933
So Ibrahim will load up...

39:22.994 --> 39:24.735
and deliver it to your office.

39:24.896 --> 39:26.341
Tell me something...

39:27.732 --> 39:30.212
Why are we dividing all the food?

39:32.871 --> 39:35.784
Why don't we all
gather at one place...

39:35.907 --> 39:37.853
and take all the stuff there.

39:38.743 --> 39:40.950
You know,
if we Indians stay together...

39:42.447 --> 39:44.393
- What happened?
- We Indians?

39:44.749 --> 39:45.250
Oh, come on!

39:45.316 --> 39:47.193
Since when did you
become an Indian, Ranjit?

39:47.252 --> 39:48.788
Weren't you always a Kuwaiti.

39:49.754 --> 39:52.667
Ranjit, let's just take the
first flight out of here.

39:53.124 --> 39:54.228
Saddam has attacked them.

39:54.292 --> 39:55.396
Why should we be bothered?

39:55.460 --> 39:56.996
What's the bother?

39:57.429 --> 39:59.807
All we need is a big space,
that's all.

40:00.298 --> 40:02.209
It's a question of
couple of days, Ranjit.

40:02.767 --> 40:04.838
- What's the problem?
- Hold on.

40:06.304 --> 40:09.342
- Ranjit is right.
- Let's solve our own problems.

40:09.874 --> 40:11.751
Trying to help 170,000..

40:12.143 --> 40:15.215
will only add to our problems.

40:16.815 --> 40:18.021
Come on, Ibrahim.

40:20.051 --> 40:21.052
Ashok...

40:23.955 --> 40:25.866
outside of this supermarket...

40:26.090 --> 40:28.195
nobody recognizes you or me.

40:28.860 --> 40:30.396
We have no standing.

40:31.429 --> 40:33.375
The only thing we
have is our identity.

40:33.498 --> 40:35.444
We're Indian, not Kuwaiti.

40:37.068 --> 40:39.810
Together we're something...

40:40.705 --> 40:41.740
If not...

40:42.874 --> 40:43.852
Nothing!

40:52.083 --> 40:55.929
It's old whiskey... but not
worth 500,000 dollars, Mr. Ranjit.

41:00.091 --> 41:01.365
I did try to tell you...

41:01.426 --> 41:04.373
Getting involved
in social work is a trap.

41:06.397 --> 41:07.842
That's not it, sir.

41:08.099 --> 41:09.100
Once the camp is set up...

41:09.167 --> 41:11.238
I'll leave with my wife and child.

41:11.803 --> 41:13.339
As long as you're with us.

41:13.404 --> 41:17.181
Aah... you're trying to flatter me.

41:19.410 --> 41:22.823
Even the President considers
Indians as friends.

41:23.214 --> 41:25.057
You can setup camp anywhere you want.

41:25.183 --> 41:27.356
- You have my permission.
- Thank you.

41:28.119 --> 41:31.760
But why take your family to the camp?

41:33.057 --> 41:35.799
Tell your wife it's safe at home.

41:36.127 --> 41:38.038
You have my word.

41:38.229 --> 41:39.230
Thank you.

42:16.868 --> 42:18.006
Come on.

42:20.204 --> 42:21.274
Excuse me.

42:54.872 --> 42:55.907
There are classrooms at the back.

42:55.973 --> 42:56.917
You can sleep there.

42:57.575 --> 42:58.815
There are bathrooms here too.

42:59.143 --> 43:01.589
There's water available
here.

43:02.747 --> 43:04.784
And Ashok's trying to find out.

43:05.717 --> 43:07.788
You see... we can put up tents here...

43:07.852 --> 43:09.957
and let people sleep.

43:10.154 --> 43:11.861
- Ranjit.
- Yes, Ashok.

43:11.923 --> 43:14.199
The canteen's on that side.
We can serve them meals in there.

43:16.227 --> 43:17.228
Simu.

43:18.196 --> 43:19.197
Simu!

43:20.264 --> 43:21.174
Simu!

43:23.201 --> 43:24.236
Simu!

43:24.869 --> 43:25.870
Simu!

43:26.771 --> 43:27.875
Simu!

43:29.073 --> 43:29.983
Simu!

43:30.408 --> 43:31.751
Mom.

43:33.111 --> 43:35.250
Simu, out of the bus!

43:36.280 --> 43:38.260
I told you to stay right here!

43:38.783 --> 43:39.625
Come on.

43:40.418 --> 43:41.192
Come here.

43:43.154 --> 43:45.691
You can stay here.

43:47.158 --> 43:49.434
This is my luggage-

43:50.161 --> 43:51.765
What do you mean by that?

43:54.666 --> 43:57.806
- This is my room.
- No, we'll shift to some other room.

43:58.336 --> 44:02.443
It should be first come, first served.

44:02.974 --> 44:04.180
I saw it first.

44:04.242 --> 44:05.414
What do you think this is...

44:05.743 --> 44:07.051
'finders keepers'?

44:07.345 --> 44:09.689
- We'll go..
- No, no, not at all.

44:09.747 --> 44:12.785
If she's okay...

44:19.123 --> 44:20.431
Nonsense!

44:21.859 --> 44:22.860
Come here.

44:30.468 --> 44:31.811
- Come on, let's go.
- No!

44:31.869 --> 44:33.871
We won't stay here.

44:34.439 --> 44:36.419
We'll all be together here.
It'll be safe.

44:36.474 --> 44:37.282
Safe!

44:37.742 --> 44:39.949
I found Simu playing with this!
A bullet!

44:41.913 --> 44:43.790
You can help them settle down,
if you want.

44:43.881 --> 44:45.155
Don't involve us.

44:46.150 --> 44:47.322
- Amrita...
- No.

44:47.819 --> 44:50.163
When you're ready,
pick us up from home.

44:50.755 --> 44:52.928
The Major has guaranteed
our safety, hasn't he?

44:55.126 --> 44:56.264
I'm leaving.

44:58.896 --> 44:59.897
Are you coming?

45:03.468 --> 45:04.811
Okay, sit.

45:11.709 --> 45:12.949
- I'll drop her home.
- Okay.

45:13.010 --> 45:14.182
Take care of things.

45:26.824 --> 45:27.962
What are you doing?

45:29.160 --> 45:30.935
Get lost.

45:30.995 --> 45:32.804
Get lost.

45:34.432 --> 45:36.036
Is this a picnic?

45:37.368 --> 45:38.472
There's a war going on...

45:38.703 --> 45:40.080
Do you have any sense?

45:40.805 --> 45:42.045
No discipline at all.

45:42.206 --> 45:43.310
Look at him screaming.

45:43.374 --> 45:44.352
Who's that?

45:44.742 --> 45:46.346
- It can be only one guy?
- Who?

45:46.811 --> 45:47.755
My husband.

45:55.019 --> 45:56.362
Let me take him...

45:56.420 --> 45:58.798
While you eat something.

46:03.895 --> 46:06.501
I'll take it... We'll eat later.

46:23.147 --> 46:24.353
Ashok, we've finished our scotch...

46:24.415 --> 46:25.894
Where is America?

46:25.950 --> 46:27.861
Forget America... Where's India?

46:28.786 --> 46:30.356
Around 150,000 Indians are stuck here.

46:30.421 --> 46:31.729
Is anyone concerned?

46:32.290 --> 46:33.462
They haven't done anything for us.

46:33.524 --> 46:35.231
It's not like we've done anything
for India either.

46:35.393 --> 46:38.374
You might
not have done anything.

46:38.429 --> 46:40.534
We send millions of Dinar to India.

46:41.165 --> 46:44.271
They want our Dinar...

46:44.936 --> 46:46.882
but they don't
care about our lives.

46:47.205 --> 46:50.118
If this had
been a western country...

46:50.274 --> 46:52.481
their embassy would've
gotten their people out by now.

46:52.844 --> 46:54.346
The embassy can do something...

46:54.412 --> 46:56.255
only if they know
that we've setup a camp.

46:56.314 --> 46:58.385
- How will they find out? When we..
- What's this?

46:59.784 --> 47:01.786
There's no discipline in the camp.

47:05.223 --> 47:06.031
What?

47:06.958 --> 47:07.993
Didn't you hear?

47:09.160 --> 47:10.298
I heard.

47:10.561 --> 47:11.767
Good.

47:19.370 --> 47:20.815
Let's go to the embassy.

47:35.019 --> 47:36.657
- Kurien, look there.
- Yes.

47:43.027 --> 47:44.904
- Where's everyone?
- Gone.

47:45.129 --> 47:45.869
Gone?

47:45.963 --> 47:47.203
Where's Brij?

47:47.431 --> 47:49.104
The entire embassy has been evacuated.

47:49.300 --> 47:50.335
I'm leaving too.

47:50.835 --> 47:53.179
Saddam says there's no point in
having two embassies in one country.

47:53.371 --> 47:54.748
All the embassies
are in Baghdad anyway.

47:54.805 --> 47:57.684
So will all the Indians
go to Baghdad now?

47:57.742 --> 47:59.415
No point yelling at me.

47:59.744 --> 48:01.155
Talk to the External
Affairs Ministry in Delhi.

48:01.312 --> 48:02.416
They'll tell you
what Indians should do.

48:02.480 --> 48:04.687
- What nonsense.
- Wait. Wait.

48:04.849 --> 48:05.953
Do you have any number?

48:06.017 --> 48:07.087
Someone we can call?

48:16.961 --> 48:18.235
Mr. Mishra, come.

48:18.996 --> 48:19.997
Come on.

48:50.795 --> 48:52.866
Hello, Ministry of External Affairs.

48:53.064 --> 48:56.204
This is Ranjit Katiyal
speaking from Kuwait city.

48:56.333 --> 48:57.107
Yes.

48:57.168 --> 48:59.079
We've been given a few numbers...

48:59.336 --> 49:01.009
By the way, who is this?

49:01.272 --> 49:04.014
Joint Secretary, Sanjeev Kohli.

49:04.075 --> 49:06.021
I wanted to talk to you about...

49:06.077 --> 49:08.216
the situation of
Indians living in Kuwait.

49:08.612 --> 49:11.320
We Indians have setup
camp in Apex School...

49:11.582 --> 49:14.358
Look,
I don't handle the Gulf Division.

49:14.685 --> 49:16.824
You've been given the wrong number.

49:16.887 --> 49:19.060
Look Mr. Kohli, we need help.

49:19.223 --> 49:21.294
And we need it right now.

49:22.059 --> 49:22.969
Well...

49:25.129 --> 49:27.609
I'll communicate this...

49:27.765 --> 49:30.678
to the Joint
Secretary of the Gulf division.

49:30.735 --> 49:32.646
Give me the number to your school.

49:39.043 --> 49:40.351
Green chilly?

49:41.045 --> 49:42.353
No, thanks.

49:42.647 --> 49:43.819
Meher! Meher!

49:46.917 --> 49:48.260
This is where we're going to live?

49:48.619 --> 49:49.825
With these people?

49:50.154 --> 49:51.792
- I'm leaving!
- Dad!

49:52.122 --> 49:54.068
They are killing people outside.

49:54.325 --> 49:56.066
Meher, Saddam has guaranteed...

49:56.127 --> 49:58.403
that Iraqis won't hurt Indians.

49:58.629 --> 49:59.403
How would they know...

49:59.630 --> 50:00.938
who's Kuwaiti, who's Indian?

50:00.998 --> 50:03.000
Meher... The bank has
my entire life's savings...

50:03.067 --> 50:04.137
not yours!

50:06.904 --> 50:07.974
I'm leaving!

50:14.879 --> 50:16.017
It's okay, dear.

50:16.180 --> 50:17.386
It'll be okay.

50:21.085 --> 50:22.359
Let me do it.

50:22.887 --> 50:24.093
Can I tie that for you.

50:24.622 --> 50:26.260
Allow me...

50:26.724 --> 50:27.634
What?

50:28.959 --> 50:29.937
What did you say?

50:29.994 --> 50:31.439
Are you Kuwaiti?

50:40.571 --> 50:41.549
You go ahead.

50:44.809 --> 50:46.152
Sheer insensitivity.

50:46.644 --> 50:49.716
There's no communication from
the External Ministry yet.

50:49.813 --> 50:51.156
- While taking our number...
- Papa!

50:51.315 --> 50:53.989
My sweetie-pie.

50:54.185 --> 50:55.892
Hello, stranger.

50:57.555 --> 51:00.126
This is the first nice
surprise after 2nd August.

51:00.724 --> 51:02.169
You hardly ever come home.

51:02.660 --> 51:04.697
So I have to bring Simu
here to see her father, don't I?

51:05.763 --> 51:06.764
Thank you.

51:09.066 --> 51:10.602
What's going on?

51:11.669 --> 51:13.171
Nothing much. We've been trying to
reach the External Affairs Ministry...

51:13.237 --> 51:14.944
in Delhi for four days,
but haven't managed to.

51:15.306 --> 51:16.148
Hello, ma'am.

51:16.240 --> 51:17.048
- How are you?
- Fine.

51:17.107 --> 51:17.744
Yes.

51:17.808 --> 51:18.718
Come, Simu.

51:18.776 --> 51:20.722
I'll show you something really nice.

51:21.612 --> 51:23.990
- Are you enjoying all this?
- What?

51:24.048 --> 51:27.621
I have no idea when you come or go.

51:28.619 --> 51:30.690
I'm trying to son all this.

51:30.888 --> 51:32.834
- Our people..
- Our people?

51:33.657 --> 51:35.000
Our people?

51:36.060 --> 51:38.973
Calling Delhi every day,
playing Indian Indian...

51:39.330 --> 51:41.037
Since when did you
star-t caring so much about them?

51:41.298 --> 51:43.574
Whenever I spoke about
going to India... - Amrita.

51:43.701 --> 51:46.614
Amrita, once we have
some clarity from Delhi..

51:46.670 --> 51:49.378
about the status of our people
we'll get out of here.

51:49.607 --> 51:50.915
- Hello, ma'am.
- Yeah.

51:54.111 --> 51:55.886
Will you answer one question?

51:56.313 --> 51:57.792
And I'm not asking in anger.

51:58.249 --> 52:00.593
Why? Why all this?

52:00.884 --> 52:01.794
Why this charade?

52:01.852 --> 52:05.800
And what are you
suddenly trying to be?

52:06.357 --> 52:07.597
Ranjit?

52:12.363 --> 52:14.673
- Look at these people.
- Why?

52:15.065 --> 52:16.203
Amrita, look at them.

52:18.402 --> 52:20.882
Some of them have been
working in our office...

52:20.938 --> 52:22.849
for 5... 10... 12 years.

52:23.841 --> 52:25.878
But I didn't even know their names.

52:26.944 --> 52:29.618
Unfortunately, now I do.

52:31.916 --> 52:33.259
If we walk away...

52:34.251 --> 52:36.356
we will be leaving these
names behind, not just any crowd.

52:37.087 --> 52:39.795
It's true, they're not related to us.

52:40.891 --> 52:42.700
But neither was Nair.

52:44.195 --> 52:45.799
And he lost his life.

52:46.130 --> 52:48.303
And it's not like I'm giving up
my life for these people.

52:51.035 --> 52:54.016
If I turn away now, won't you ask...

52:54.438 --> 52:56.782
"Ranjit, what kind of a man are you?"

52:59.843 --> 53:00.981
Ranjit!

53:06.917 --> 53:08.863
Sir, we're Indians.

53:09.019 --> 53:10.760
We have permission.

53:12.022 --> 53:13.296
We have permission.

53:46.390 --> 53:50.463
- Ismail, Mani. Go hide the food.
- Okay.

55:51.648 --> 55:53.628
Good to see you, Mr. Ranjit.

55:53.984 --> 55:56.624
Where's my whiskey today?

55:59.156 --> 56:00.726
Your soldiers came...

56:00.791 --> 56:02.270
They looted our camp.

56:02.626 --> 56:03.798
I am sorry.

56:03.961 --> 56:05.804
But what can they do?

56:05.863 --> 56:07.809
Baghdad sent us...

56:07.998 --> 56:10.069
but forgot our supplies.

56:10.567 --> 56:13.605
They thought we could depend
on your hospitality.

56:13.837 --> 56:16.249
But... why are you so worried?

56:16.640 --> 56:18.847
It's not like they
really did anything to you.

56:19.009 --> 56:19.885
Did they?

56:19.977 --> 56:21.183
Maybe they will come back.

56:21.245 --> 56:22.349
I can't stop them.

56:22.579 --> 56:24.581
How do I ensure the
safety of my people?

56:25.315 --> 56:28.228
Ranjit! Ranjit! Ranjit!

56:28.652 --> 56:32.293
Now I know for sure you're trapped.

56:32.756 --> 56:35.760
You can all leave Kuwait
anytime if you want.

56:36.126 --> 56:39.300
The President, like me, is
a friend of Indians.

56:39.630 --> 56:42.008
And he has already
permitted Indians to leave.

56:42.066 --> 56:46.310
- You never told me that.
- You never asked.

56:46.604 --> 56:48.049
And that's why you never told me?

56:49.706 --> 56:50.844
May Allah be with you.

56:56.914 --> 56:59.258
But Ranjit... tell me..

57:00.083 --> 57:03.189
Where will you go
with all these people?

57:07.057 --> 57:09.435
- Yes, sir?
- Joseph. My medicines are almost over.

57:09.860 --> 57:10.964
I'll look into it, sir.

57:11.295 --> 57:14.071
What if the soldiers come back?

57:14.131 --> 57:15.201
There's nothing we can do, sir.

57:15.265 --> 57:16.938
- Joseph.
- Yes, sir.

57:17.067 --> 57:18.068
Excuse me.

57:18.769 --> 57:20.214
Make a list...

57:20.337 --> 57:21.338
of the people here.

57:21.705 --> 57:22.683
Write down all their names.

57:22.739 --> 57:24.275
We should know how
many people are here.

57:24.741 --> 57:25.913
And what are we doing about food now?

57:25.976 --> 57:27.785
Sir, we still have food for 2-3 days.

57:27.844 --> 57:30.723
Ibrahim managed
to hide half the food.

57:32.850 --> 57:34.727
Thank God.
Well, that's good.

57:35.319 --> 57:37.526
But why are you calling me?

57:37.754 --> 57:40.166
I already passed on
the number to the Gulf Desk.

57:40.324 --> 57:41.997
Sir, no one has called
from the Ministry yet.

57:42.059 --> 57:43.231
And they probably never will.

57:43.360 --> 57:45.362
- I need your help.
- What?

57:45.729 --> 57:48.141
Look, Saddam Hussain has permitted...

57:48.198 --> 57:50.269
us Indians to get out of Kuwait.

57:51.001 --> 57:52.742
But we don't know where to go...

57:52.803 --> 57:53.975
when or how?

57:54.037 --> 57:56.779
If you could help us,
then it'll be really great.

57:56.840 --> 57:59.946
Let me speak to the
Minister and call you back.

58:02.813 --> 58:03.382
Okay.

58:03.747 --> 58:04.691
Yes, Kohli.

58:04.781 --> 58:06.886
Those Indians stuck in Kuwait...

58:06.950 --> 58:09.157
Talk to Sharma at the Gulf Desk.

58:09.286 --> 58:11.129
Sir, if you could just
put in a word.

58:11.188 --> 58:13.691
Kohli! The Prime
Minister's waiting for me.

58:14.024 --> 58:14.832
Hurry HP!

58:16.894 --> 58:18.703
Father's name, Vasudevan.

58:19.129 --> 58:20.073
Trichur.

58:20.197 --> 58:21.369
Okay, please.

58:21.832 --> 58:22.936
Next.

58:32.009 --> 58:33.283
We must tell sir now.

58:38.782 --> 58:40.386
Ibrahim, have you lost your mind?

58:41.418 --> 58:43.056
You shouldn't have
hidden this from me!

58:43.787 --> 58:46.324
If those Iraqi soldiers
had found out...

58:47.090 --> 58:48.763
that she's a Kuwaiti.

58:50.060 --> 58:52.233
They would've shot
everyone in the camp.

58:54.665 --> 58:56.440
Sir, I didn't think about that.

58:56.733 --> 58:59.976
I only thought about what
they would've done to her.

59:06.109 --> 59:07.417
But honestly, sir...

59:07.778 --> 59:11.157
what is the proof
that we're not Kuwaiti.

59:12.015 --> 59:14.325
Most of them don't have any documents.

59:15.118 --> 59:16.756
Agents have their passports.

59:17.321 --> 59:18.959
Who will believe we're Indian?

59:28.866 --> 59:30.174
Mr. Ranjit Katiyal.

59:30.434 --> 59:33.108
Look, I couldn't find out much.

59:33.170 --> 59:35.446
But I was informed
by the Gulf Division that...

59:35.972 --> 59:38.452
you could possibly go to Jordan.

59:38.909 --> 59:40.115
Possibly?

59:41.278 --> 59:45.385
But Mr. Kohli,
many of us don't have passports.

59:45.516 --> 59:49.020
- What do we do?
- I don't know about that.

59:49.286 --> 59:50.458
But...

59:51.455 --> 59:53.765
Do you have any contacts in Baghdad?

59:54.525 --> 59:55.731
Are you crazy?

59:56.860 --> 59:57.998
He'll go to Iraq?

59:58.895 --> 01:00:00.135
Do you think it's a picnic?

01:00:00.831 --> 01:00:02.936
Those boy soldiers,
who haven't even reached puberty...

01:00:03.033 --> 01:00:03.943
Crazy!

01:00:04.201 --> 01:00:06.272
Ashok, what choice do we have?

01:00:06.770 --> 01:00:09.080
You said that so easily
but what choice do we have?

01:00:10.741 --> 01:00:12.379
Those crazy Iraqis
can come back anytime.

01:00:12.442 --> 01:00:13.921
They can blow up
our school.

01:00:13.977 --> 01:00:15.012
And what can we do?

01:00:15.345 --> 01:00:17.382
Isn't it better that I go to Baghdad?

01:00:17.447 --> 01:00:20.018
Talk to some people.
I know some people.

01:00:20.217 --> 01:00:21.560
We must do something.

01:00:21.952 --> 01:00:24.023
We can't just sit here
with our hands tied.

01:00:30.994 --> 01:00:32.769
Sir, there's a hospital up ahead.

01:00:33.230 --> 01:00:34.573
Can we stop there for a minute...

01:00:34.898 --> 01:00:36.935
If you don't mind...

01:00:37.968 --> 01:00:38.776
Thank you.

01:01:19.943 --> 01:01:21.547
Sorry for the trouble, sir.

01:01:21.778 --> 01:01:23.223
Come on, let's get out of here.

01:02:06.089 --> 01:02:06.931
Paper.

01:02:07.023 --> 01:02:07.967
Paper.

01:02:08.825 --> 01:02:10.236
Indian. Indian.

01:02:10.927 --> 01:02:12.235
Sticker!

01:02:16.967 --> 01:02:18.810
How did he get this?

01:02:19.369 --> 01:02:20.404
Okay, let him go!

01:02:20.737 --> 01:02:22.239
Open the way!

01:02:23.306 --> 01:02:25.980
- Go! Go!
- Thank you!

01:02:40.757 --> 01:02:42.236
Is someone at the hospital?

01:02:43.393 --> 01:02:45.430
I got married 8 days ago.

01:02:46.163 --> 01:02:48.473
My bride's name is Shazin.

01:02:49.299 --> 01:02:50.937
The ceremony was
to be two days later...

01:02:51.068 --> 01:02:52.547
along with the send-off.

01:02:53.036 --> 01:02:56.313
But... Saddam sent
his cavalry that night.

01:02:57.941 --> 01:03:01.047
Shazin is a nurse at the hospital.

01:03:01.444 --> 01:03:03.549
And she's been busy
at the hospital since then?

01:03:03.813 --> 01:03:04.985
No, sir. She's not at the hospital...

01:03:05.048 --> 01:03:07.187
nor was she at home.

01:03:07.484 --> 01:03:09.486
I've been looking for her...

01:03:09.853 --> 01:03:11.423
but I haven't
found any trace of her.

01:03:25.836 --> 01:03:28.646
Don't go, Ranjit. It's not safe.

01:03:30.607 --> 01:03:32.951
Why don't you understand
me these days?

01:03:33.710 --> 01:03:37.157
Neither of us understands the other.

01:03:38.014 --> 01:03:41.257
It's the circumstances
that are wrong... Not us.

01:03:41.718 --> 01:03:46.963
"L am going to love you so much."

01:03:47.657 --> 01:03:52.970
I'm going to love
you 100 times in a moment.

01:03:53.964 --> 01:03:59.642
"If you ever live me."

01:03:59.903 --> 01:04:04.943
"I will only wait for death."

01:04:05.575 --> 01:04:08.317
"I've forsaken the world for you."

01:04:08.678 --> 01:04:11.591
"My breath stops on you."

01:04:11.681 --> 01:04:14.161
"I love you so much."

01:04:14.618 --> 01:04:17.599
